; SAE J2534-1 v04.04 PassThru API — v04.04 ONLY.
;
; This DLL supports v04.04 and NOT v05.00. The 14 v04.04 functions below
; are all that's exported, and that is by design. Names match the C
; signatures in j2534.h. Without this .def the __stdcall decorator suffix
; and x64 mangling would surface — apps load these by exact name via
; GetProcAddress.
;
; LIBRARY directive intentionally omitted so the linker doesn't override
; the project's TargetName (PassThruShim32.dll / PassThruShim64.dll).
EXPORTS
    PassThruOpen
    PassThruClose
    PassThruConnect
    PassThruDisconnect
    PassThruReadMsgs
    PassThruWriteMsgs
    PassThruStartPeriodicMsg
    PassThruStopPeriodicMsg
    PassThruStartMsgFilter
    PassThruStopMsgFilter
    PassThruSetProgrammingVoltage
    PassThruReadVersion
    PassThruGetLastError
    PassThruIoctl
;
; Intentionally NOT exported (NOT a v04.04 function — do not add):
;   PassThruScanForDevices, PassThruGetNextDevice,
;   PassThruLogicalConnect, PassThruLogicalDisconnect,
;   PassThruSelect, PassThruQueueMsgs        <- all v05.00
;   PassThruGetNextCarDAQ                    <- Drew Tech proprietary;
;       triggers an x64 AV inside J2534-Sharp's HeapIntPtr (4-byte alloc,
;       8-byte ReadIntPtr) on the first call.
;
; Hosts that gate connection on a non-empty GetDeviceList must instead
; call api.GetDevice("") for the default device — that's the v04.04
; spec-defined open path.
